translated: Engdahl, Carl Gustaf, Lieutenant Colonel, born on January 7th, 1895 in Sorunda, Stockholm County, son of Karl Herman E. and Anna Maria Gagner. Married on the 21st of an unknown month in an unknown year to Greta Falck. They have one child named Torsten, born in 1937. Engdahl passed the Officer's Exam in 1916, attended the Allmänna Artilleriläroverket (AIHS) general course from 1918-1919, and the higher course from 1920-1922. He was promoted to Second Lieutenant in the Värmlands Artillery Regiment in 1919, to Lieutenant later the same year, to Captain in 1931, to Major in the Småland Artillery Regiment in 1938, and to Lieutenant Colonel in 1941. He was a teacher in ballistics at the Royal Swedish Army Staff College from 1929-1937 and wrote the textbook "Lärobok i vapenlära f. KS" in 1936. He received the Royal Order of the Sword, Military Athletic Association Medal, Shooting Medal, Skiing Medal, and Swedish Sports Federation Medal, as well as being a member of the Swedish Swimming Federation's Swimming Hall of Fame.
